+
+# ALOHA Evaluation (`eval_aloha.py`)
+
+This folder provides an evaluation script for the ALOHA pipeline that can run:
+
+- **MuJoCo simulation** (`--robot_type mujoco_aloha`) for tasks like `sim_transfer_cube`.
+- **Real ALOHA robot** (`--robot_type real_aloha`) for tasks like `transfer_cube`.
+
+It supports three inference modes:
+
+- **PyTorch** (default)
+- **OpenVINO** (`--use_ov` + `--ov_model_path ...`)
+- **OpenVINO + RTC** (`--use_ov` + `--rtc_enabled`)
+
+## Environment Setup
+
+The script depends on different components depending on the robot type:
+
+- **MuJoCo simulation**: requires a working dm_control / MuJoCo setup. For headless rendering on Linux, set `MUJOCO_GL=egl`.
+- **Real ALOHA**: requires the ALOHA hardware stack and ROS dependencies (e.g. `aloha`, `interbotix_common_modules`, etc.).
+
+## Run Examples
+
+### 1) Run `sim_transfer_cube` in MuJoCo (PyTorch model)
+
+```bash
+MUJOCO_GL=egl python examples/aloha/eval_aloha.py \
+	--robot_type mujoco_aloha \
+	--task sim_transfer_cube \
+	--pretrained_model_path <path_to_pretrained_model>
+```
+
+### 2) Run `sim_transfer_cube` in MuJoCo using an OpenVINO model
+
+```bash
+MUJOCO_GL=egl python examples/aloha/eval_aloha.py \
+	--robot_type mujoco_aloha \
+	--task sim_transfer_cube \
+    --pretrained_model_path <path_to_pretrained_model> \
+	--use_ov \
+	--ov_model_path <path_to_ov_model>
+```
+
+Note: Even when using `--use_ov`, you still need to provide `--pretrained_model_path`. It is used to construct the model inputs (preprocessing/tokenization), and determine model/config dimensions (e.g. action space) alongside the OpenVINO model.
+
+Note: For correct normalization, you should also provide dataset statistics via `--stats_path` (recommended) or `--dataset_path`. If neither is provided, the script will try to load `stats.json` from `--pretrained_model_path`.
+
+### 3) Run `transfer_cube` on a real ALOHA robot using an OpenVINO model
+
+```bash
+python examples/aloha/eval_aloha.py \
+	--robot_type real_aloha \
+	--task transfer_cube \
+	--max_steps 600 \
+	--pretrained_model_path <path_to_pretrained_model> \
+	--use_ov \
+	--ov_model_path <path_to_ov_model>
+```
+
+### 4) Run `transfer_cube` on a real ALOHA robot using OpenVINO + RTC
+
+```bash
+python examples/aloha/eval_aloha.py \
+	--robot_type real_aloha \
+	--task transfer_cube \
+	--max_steps 600 \
+	--pretrained_model_path <path_to_pretrained_model> \
+	--use_ov \
+	--ov_model_path <path_to_ov_model> \
+	--rtc_enabled \
+    --rtc_horizon 30
+```
+
+Tips: When running OpenVINO inference on Intel ARL platforms, pinning the process to P-cores can help achieve more stable inference performance. For example, prefix your command with `taskset`:
+
+```bash
+taskset -c 0-5 \
+  python examples/aloha/eval_aloha.py ...
+```
+
+## Arguments
+
+- `--pretrained_model_path`: Path to the pretrained model checkpoint or Hugging Face repo id. Default: `lerobot/pi05_base`.
+- `--pretrained_model_path`: Path to the pretrained model checkpoint or Hugging Face repo id. Default: `lerobot/pi05_base`.
+- `--dataset_path`: (Optional) Local dataset directory used to load metadata (e.g. task language) and, if needed, dataset statistics.
+- `--stats_path`: (Optional) Path to `stats.json` used for normalization. If omitted, the script will try to use `<pretrained_model_path>/stats.json`, and then fall back to stats from `--dataset_path` if available.
+- `--robot_type`: `mujoco_aloha` or `real_aloha`.
+- `--task`: Task name, e.g. `sim_transfer_cube`, `sim_insertion`, `transfer_cube`.
+- `--num_episodes`: Number of episodes to run. Default: `1`.
+- `--max_steps`: Max steps per episode. Default: `400`.
+
+**RTC (Real-Time Chunking):**
+
+- `--rtc_enabled`: Enable RTC logic.
+- `--rtc_horizon`: Execution horizon for RTC. Default: `30`.
+
+**OpenVINO:**
+
+- `--use_ov`: Use OpenVINO model for inference.
+- `--ov_model_path`: Path to an OpenVINO IR model directory (should contain `model.xml` and `model.bin`). Default: `pi05_lerobot_ov_ir_INT8`.
+- `--ov_device`: OpenVINO device string (e.g. `CPU`, `GPU`, `GPU.0`). Default: `GPU.0`.
+
+Note: OpenVINO inference still requires `--pretrained_model_path`. Dataset statistics are also needed for normalization; provide them via `--stats_path` (recommended) or `--dataset_path`.
+
+**Debug/Logging:**
+
+- `--plot`: Enable visualization (typically used with MuJoCo).
+- `--save_traj`: Save trajectory data and plots.
+- `--save_traj_path`: Output directory for saved trajectories/plots. Default: `trajectory_plots`.
+
